<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3361] port url+email tokenizer to standardtokenizerinterface (or similar)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3361</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;We should do this so that we can fix the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3358&quot; title=&quot;StandardTokenizer disposes of Hiragana combining mark dakuten instead of attaching it to the character it belongs to&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3358&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; bug there, and preserve backwards.&lt;br/&gt;
We also want this mechanism anyway, for upgrading to new unicode versions in the future.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can regenerate the new TLD list for 3.4 but, we should ensure the existing one is used for the urlemail33 or whatever,&lt;br/&gt;
so that its exactly the same.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
